{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 180°C. Grease 6 ramekins or flan dishes (125 ml capacity). Divide berries equally between ramekins and set aside.","Place almonds into mixing bowl and mill <nobr>15 sec\/speed 9<\/nobr> or until finely ground.","Add flour, milk, honey and eggs and blend <nobr>10 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr> or until well combined and smooth. Pour batter over berries and dot with butter. Bake for 25-30 minutes (180°C), or until tops are golden and batter has set. Serve warm drizzled with extra honey and yoghurt (optional). "]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["1 tbsp butter, plus extra for greasing","200 g mixed berries (see Tips)","40 g almonds (raw or roasted)","2 tbsp wholemeal flour","190 g milk","60 g honey, plus extra to serve","2 eggs","plain yoghurt, to serve (optional)"]}],"id":"r122267","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-5VkizLVIpa8\/XZWrE6uHovI\/AAAAAAAAfhw\/4b52RQOsgNMWisg6G7ffOUTD0OuvO-66gCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_bl67dq2N8ixSxPYn.png","title":"Mixed berry clafoutis","publishedAt":"2017-04-02T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"6.2 g","fat":"15.1 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"18.3 g","calories":"976 kJ \/ 232 kcal"},"usefulItems":"6 ramekins (8 cm, 125 ml), oven","hintsAndTricks":["Use a selection of berries, such as raspberries, blueberries, blackberries, mulberries and\/or pitted cherries.","Frozen and fresh berries both work well in these clafoutis."],"basicInfo":["easy","5m","40m","6 portions"]}